== Addition + ==

Natural number addition is defined recursively through the [/wiki/peano/arithmetic/axioms | Peano axioms] using the
[/wiki/peano/arithmetic/successor | successor] operation. Natural number addition is used to 
[/wiki/peano/arithmetic/integers | construct integer addition]. Integer addition is used to 
[/wiki/peano/arithmetic/rationals | construct rational addition].

=== Properties ===

* Commutation: A + B = B + A ([/edit/peano/peano_thms.gh/addcom | natural], [/edit/peano/integers.gh/zaddcom | integer], [/edit/peano/rationals.gh/qaddcom | rational])
* Association: (A + B) + C = A + (B + C) ([/edit/peano/peano_thms.gh/addass | natural], [/edit/peano/integers.gh/zaddass | integers], [/edit/peano/rationals.gh/qaddass | rational])
* Identity: A + 0 = A ([edit/peano/peano_min.ghi/pa_ax3 | natural], [/edit/peano/integers.gh/zaddid | integer], [/edit/peano/rationals.gh/qaddid | rational])
* Distribution: A∙(B + C) = A∙B + A∙C ([/edit/peano/peano_thms.gh/distr | natural], [/edit/peano/integers.gh/zdistr | integer], [/edit/peano/rationals.gh/qdistr | rational])

